GETCHA
Chapter 1 Cutscene Scripts
Ashes of Oath

Format Note
This file converts the Chapter 1 storyboard into mission-ready cutscene and dialogue beats. Each mission section includes a pre-mission cinematic, battle-start flavor, and post-mission outcome. Optional camp scenes are included where they add character development.


OPENING CUTSCENE
Cutscene ID: c1_opening_ceremony
Location: High Court of the capital
Cast: Aric, Lyria, The Lord Marshall, Captain Elowen, court assembly

Visual Direction
Wide shot over the capital at dawn. White towers blaze gold in morning light. Crimson and ivory banners lift in the wind. Courtiers in ceremonial regalia line the court. Music is noble, triumphant, and just slightly too polished.

Script
The Lord Marshall: "Aric, shield of the realm, you have carried this kingdom through fire and returned its people to peace time and again."

Aric: "I have only done my duty, my lord."

Lyria, aside: "If they carve that on your grave, I am haunting the sculptor."

Aric: "You assume I plan to die first."

Lyria: "I assume if you do, it will be while frowning heroically."

Light court laughter. Aric almost smiles.

Captain Elowen enters quickly, kneels, and presents a sealed dispatch.

Captain Elowen: "Urgent reports from Whispering Woods. Raids at Verdant Clearing. Missing scouts. Survivors claim the attackers moved with military precision."

The Lord Marshall: "Then we act before fear spreads faster than truth. Aric, go at once. Keep the force small. Quiet answers are often the cleanest."

He steps close and lowers his tone.

The Lord Marshall: "Bring them home. The realm still needs its shield."

Aric kneels.

Aric: "By your command."

End Beat
Close on the Lord Marshall's hand on Aric's shoulder. Hold one beat too long. Music dips into unease.


OPTIONAL FLASHBACK 001
Cutscene ID: c1_autumn_lessons
Location: Aric's childhood home, years earlier
Cast: Young Aric, Younger Lord Marshall

Visual Direction
On the uneasy note, hard cut to warm autumn light over a modest courtyard. Leaves tumble across worn steps. A young Aric swings a wooden toy sword between bouts of laughter.

Script
Young Aric: "Uncle, did you see that one? I got three at once."

Younger Lord Marshall, from his bench: "I did. You nearly conquered the whole orchard."

Young Aric pauses, frowning at a faint shimmer around his hand.

Young Aric: "Why does the light keep following me?"

The Lord Marshall kneels to his height.

Younger Lord Marshall: "Because you have a special gift. You are an Oath-Weaver, Aric."

Young Aric: "Is that like being good with a sword?"

Younger Lord Marshall: "Partly. But stronger. Most people can promise things. Oath-Weavers make promises the world can hear."

He draws two circles in the dust with a fingertip.

Younger Lord Marshall: "Think of it like two knots. One in your heart. One in the world. If both hold, power flows between them."

Young Aric: "Then I will make strong knots."

End Beat
As he swings his toy sword again, a faint sigil pulses in the autumn air behind him. Leaves cross the glow. Hard cut back to present-day Aric in the capital court.


MISSION 001
Mission: Into the Clearing
Location: Verdant Clearing

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Aric and Lyria survey flattened grass, crude signal totems, and fresh tracks cut through morning mist.

Lyria: "Goblin scouts, wolves, and a perimeter line. Someone taught this patch of forest manners. Violent ones."

Aric: "Then we break the line before they warn the next nest."

Lyria: "That was almost witty. I should mark the date."

Aric: "Focus."

Battle Start Lines
Aric: "No signals leave this clearing."
Lyria: "Stars above, try to keep up."

Post-Mission Outcome
A wounded villager is pulled from an overturned cart.

Villager: "They did not raid for food. They watched the road. They wanted us moving."

Aric: "A screen operation. Not random violence."

Lyria: "That would explain why I hate this already."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 001
Location: Forward camp outside Verdant Clearing

Lyria hands Aric a cup of field tea.

Lyria: "If you stare at that fire any harder, it will surrender."

Aric: "I am thinking."

Lyria: "No. You are brooding. Different posture."

Aric: "Do you ever stop making light of things?"

Lyria: "Only when the dark is winning."

Aric finally smiles.


MISSION 002
Mission: The Pack's Cry
Location: Deeper Whispering Woods

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Wolf howls echo in measured intervals. A hidden clutch of villagers is found sheltering inside split roots.

Elderly Villager: "Our scouts vanished near marked trees. We found this."

She hands Aric a scrap bearing a strange, crown-like insignia.

Lyria: "Too neat for bandits. Too deliberate for beasts."

Aric: "Then whoever is behind this wants to be mistaken for chaos."

Battle Start Lines
Aric: "Protect the civilians. Break the herd pattern."
Lyria: "And if anyone has complaints, they can file them with my magic."

Post-Mission Outcome
Aric recovers a stamped leather token from a fallen handler.

Aric: "Missing scouts. Marked routes. Coordinated attacks."

Lyria, quieter: "I would prefer monsters. People choose this."


MISSION 003
Mission: Edge of the Woods
Location: Forest boundary

Pre-Mission Cinematic
A masked figure waits on a fallen trunk where the woods thin into open ground.

Kain: "If I meant to kill you, General, we would not be having this conversation."

Aric: "Name yourself."

Kain: "Kain. I track lies for a living. Yours have been expensive."

Lyria: "I cannot decide if that was dramatic or rude."

Kain: "It was efficient."

He shows Aric ledger scraps tied to supply payments and false tax routes.

Kain: "Someone is funding these raids. Not with gutter coin. With real backing."

Battle Start Lines
Kain: "I will take the archers. Try not to die before I return."
Aric: "Stay in formation or leave."
Lyria: "Oh, this will be fun."

Post-Mission Outcome
Kain tosses Aric a military-minted coin.

Kain: "Capital issue. Your enemy shops well."

Aric: "Why bring this to me?"

Kain: "Because if rot reaches the throne, the kingdom needs one honest man close enough to smell it."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 002
Location: Woodland camp

Lyria: "You could have opened with something less hostile."

Kain: "I could also juggle knives. Neither would improve the truth."

Aric: "Enough. If you are staying, you will speak plainly."

Kain: "Plainly? Fine. I do not trust your crown. I trust your disgust. That is why I am here."


TRANSITION CUTSCENE
Cutscene ID: c1_elowen_authority
Location: Forward command road
Cast: Aric, Lyria, Kain, Captain Elowen

Captain Elowen arrives with fresh reports and a private royal seal.

Captain Elowen: "Three attacks. Same hour. Different routes. Whoever designed this wanted you stretched thin."

Lyria: "Expanded authority? That is no small favor."

Kain leans in toward the parchment.

Kain: "Fresh wax. Wrong smell."

Aric: "Explain."

Kain: "Ash. Volcanic. Not city resin. This letter passed through ember country before it reached you."

End Beat
Aric tightens his hand around the seal.


LORE INTERLUDE 001
Cutscene ID: c1_thane_sigil_warning
Location: Command tent, same night
Cast: Aric, Lyria, Kain, Brother Thane

Brother Thane unrolls a vellum chart of sigil circles mapped against star positions and prism node marks.

Brother Thane: "These are First Era Oath-Weave schematics. Originals. Not copies."

Kain: "Translate."

Brother Thane: "Almost no one can carry an oath sigil without breaking. Fewer can synchronize two sigils in one combat line. Celestial weavers are the exception."

He looks at Lyria.

Brother Thane: "Her starlight signature can harmonize with patterns that usually reject each other."

Lyria: "You make me sound like a key."

Brother Thane: "In military terms, you are. In theological terms, you are an argument still in progress."

Aric: "And the prisms?"

Brother Thane: "Built so oath-bound defenders could be called again in eras of collapse. Not everyone can summon them safely."

Kain: "So whoever controls the prism vaults controls reinforcement itself."

A long pause.

Brother Thane: "Yes."


MISSION 004
Mission: Mushroom Labyrinth
Location: Deeproot Hollow

Pre-Mission Cinematic
The party enters luminous root tunnels and finds Sera defending trapped civilians in a narrow corridor.

Sera: "If you are here to prey on the helpless, line up and die in order."

Lyria: "I like her immediately."

Aric steps beside Sera and raises his weapon.

Aric: "We are here to get them out."

Battle Start Lines
Sera: "Hold the corridor. No one passes us."
Aric: "Move the wounded behind our line."

Post-Mission Outcome
Sera binds a child's wound before answering Aric.

Sera: "You chose the trapped before the pursuit. That is not how most officers think."

Aric: "Then most officers think wrongly."

Sera: "I will accompany you. For now."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 003
Location: Deeproot camp

Sera: "Rank is not honor. It is obligation."

Aric: "I know."

Sera: "Then remember it when the truth asks more of you than obedience does."


MISSION 005
Mission: Root Warrens
Location: Lower warrens and canopy break

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Bandits spring an ambush from the upper walkways. Lightning answers before Aric can issue the second order.

Zephyr drops into frame in a burst of stormlight.

Zephyr: "You all looked terribly outnumbered. It offended my sense of balance."

Kain: "Who makes an entrance during an ambush?"

Zephyr: "People with standards."

Battle Start Lines
Zephyr: "I will take the loud route."
Kain: "That narrows nothing down."

Post-Mission Outcome
Zephyr bows extravagantly.

Zephyr: "Zephyr. Storm caller. Occasional hero. Reliable threat to dull conversation."

Lyria: "You will fit in terribly well."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 004
Location: Root Warren camp

Kain: "Stealth gets you through alive."

Zephyr: "Style gets remembered."

Kain: "By your enemies."

Zephyr: "Exactly. Fear is branding."

Sera nearly smiles.


MISSION 006
Mission: Hollow's Heart
Location: Deep root chamber

Pre-Mission Cinematic
A swamp shaman channels hostile aether at the chamber's center beneath stolen banners and sealed packets.

Lyria: "This is not a border ritual. Someone taught him structure."

Aric: "Then we end it here and take whatever answers remain."

Battle Start Lines
Aric: "Break the altar."
Lyria: "With pleasure."

Post-Mission Outcome
Brother Thane examines recovered orders with shaking hands.

Brother Thane: "This royal cipher should not exist outside the vault. Not in the field. Not like this."

Aric: "Can it be forged?"

Brother Thane: "Not cleanly. Either someone stole the court's authority... or the court gave it."

Tag Scene
Aric later receives a private letter from the Lord Marshall.

The Lord Marshall's Letter: "Trust no one beyond your command. Move for Ashfield Pass. Burn what must be burned before it reaches the heart."

Kain: "Fresh seal. Same ash smell. Someone wants you walking into fire with your eyes closed."


PART I ENDING BEAT
Location: Departure from Deeproot Hollow

Lyria: "You are thinking too loudly again."

Aric: "Every road ahead ends in a worse question."

Kain: "Good. Questions survive longer than faith."


MISSION 007
Mission: Smoldering Trail
Location: Ashfield Pass

Pre-Mission Cinematic
The party reaches a shattered barricade and finds Draven holding the line with battered survivors.

Draven: "About time. I was starting to think the capital had run out of competent help."

Aric: "Draven."

Draven: "Still impossible to bury, I see."

Battle Start Lines
Draven: "Hit hard. Mourn later."
Aric: "Protect the survivors."

Post-Mission Outcome
Aric looks over Draven's fallen unit.

Aric: "How many?"

Draven: "Enough. We held for civilians. No order told us to. We did it because someone had to be better than the order."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 005
Location: Ashfield camp

Draven: "We used to think loyalty solved everything."

Aric: "Without loyalty, the realm falls apart."

Draven: "And if loyalty is what they use to steer good men into evil?"

Aric does not answer.


MISSION 008
Mission: Bandit Crossing
Location: Raider toll bridge

Pre-Mission Cinematic
The bridge is dressed in iron chains, warning stakes, and bodies left as trophies.

Kain: "Too obvious. They want us angry. Angry soldiers miss traps."

Draven: "Cautious soldiers leave innocents to bleed at toll gates."

Sera: "Argue after the living are safe."

Lyria quietly pulls Aric aside.

Lyria: "I know that look."

Aric: "Which one?"

Lyria: "The one where you think holding everyone together means breaking privately."

Aric finally says it.

Aric: "I am afraid, Lyria."

Lyria: "Good. It means your heart still knows this matters."

Battle Start Lines
Aric: "Take the bridge and keep the rear clear."
Zephyr: "I can do dramatic and practical at the same time."

Post-Mission Outcome
The crossing is secured, but no one celebrates.

Kain: "We won. That is not the same thing as being safe."


MISSION 009
Mission: Scorched Watchtower
Location: Enemy relay tower

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Supply crates are stacked in military order behind burned stone and hide screens.

Lyria: "That is quartermaster discipline. Not bandit instinct."

Aric: "Then someone taught them how to wage a campaign."

Battle Start Lines
Sera: "Take the stairs. Hold each landing."
Kain: "I will find the signal post."

Post-Mission Outcome
Lyria breaks open a crate and reveals a secret armory mark.

Lyria: "Aric... this belongs to royal stock."

Aric: "No."

Kain: "That word is falling behind events."

Sera: "If truth condemns the throne, what does duty become?"


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 006A
Location: Cinder Keep approach road, after Mirel's arrival
Cast: Lyria, Mirel

Lyria stays behind as the others move survivors toward safer ground.

Lyria: "You listen like a healer and a confessor at the same time."

Mirel, faint smile: "People breathe easier when they are heard before they are treated."

Lyria: "Then we should travel together more. I patch wounds with starlight. You patch the parts starlight cannot reach."

Mirel glances toward Sera, who is quietly re-wrapping a civilian's bandage.

Mirel: "And her?"

Lyria, soft: "She carries herself like a wall. Walls open slowly. We give her time."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 006B
Location: Same road, shortly after
Cast: Lyria, Mirel, Sera

Lyria arrives with warmed water and kneels beside them without ceremony.

Lyria: "I brought tea. It is objectively terrible, but it is warm."

Mirel accepts the first cup.

Mirel: "Warm is enough tonight."

Sera hesitates. Then takes the second cup.

Sera: "I am not practiced at... this kind of company."

Lyria, gentle grin: "Good. Neither are we. We can learn badly together."

Sera exhales something close to a laugh, brief and surprised.

Sera: "Very well. For now, we keep watch together."


MISSION 010
Mission: Iron Gate
Location: Outer defenses of Cinder Keep

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Ancient runes awaken across the keep's gatehouse. Stone golems rise as if answering a command sent years ago and triggered now.

Mirel appears amid survivors, drawing water over burned skin and clearing ash-choked lungs.

Mirel: "Questions later. Lift with me now."

After the wounded are moved, she addresses Aric.

Mirel: "I watched men in royal colors burn villages from the safe side of the wind. They left one escape route open. Panic corridors."

Aric: "You are certain?"

Mirel: "I am certain enough to be angry."

Battle Start Lines
Mirel: "I will cool the magma channels. Move when I say."
Aric: "Break the gate before the runes re-align."

Post-Mission Outcome
Lyria studies the keep walls.

Lyria: "These patterns are not only defensive. They gather aether inward."

Kain: "Toward what?"

Lyria: "I think we are walking toward the answer."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 006
Location: Shrine ruin near Cinder Keep

Sera: "I was taught faith would make the righteous path visible."

Mirel: "And has it?"

Sera: "No. But it has kept me walking when the path vanished."

Mirel: "Then perhaps it has done enough for tonight."


MISSION 011
Mission: The Armory
Location: Sealed armory corridors

Pre-Mission Cinematic
The party finds civilians cornered by venom traps and basilisks. A dark figure reaches them first.

Draven: "There. Cursed steel."

Kain: "Watch first. Judge second."

Vex cuts down hostile sentries, then takes venom across his arm to clear a path for the trapped civilians.

Vex: "Move."

Aric: "Why help us?"

Vex: "Because what wakes below this keep will not care who fed it. Only who remains."

Battle Start Lines
Vex: "Do not slow me down."
Zephyr: "Some people really do not rehearse small talk."

Post-Mission Outcome
Vex vanishes before the party can stop him.

Draven: "A monster can spare a child and still be a monster."

Kain: "So can a king."


OPTIONAL CAMP SCENE 007
Location: Staging chamber before Furnace Hall

Aric: "I believed service made the hand clean."

Lyria: "Service does not decide that. Choice does."

Aric: "I am afraid I have been a weapon for the wrong cause."

Lyria: "A weapon would never ask. A good man does."


MISSION 012
Mission: Furnace Hall
Location: Magma-lit throne room of Cinder Keep

Pre-Mission Cinematic
Twinfang Chief waits on a black-iron dais beneath hanging chains and roaring furnaces. The room is a savage mockery of royal splendor.

Twinfang Chief: "So the crown sends its favorite hound. Tell me, Aric, when they pointed you here, did you wag or bare teeth?"

Aric: "I came for the people you butchered."

Twinfang Chief laughs.

Twinfang Chief: "Then you came for the work of better masters than me."

Battle Start Lines
Aric: "End this. Now."
Twinfang Chief: "Come prove you were worth the leash."

Mid-Battle Beat
The Rage Cyclops crashes through a furnace gate. Draven takes a devastating blow meant for Aric.

Aric: "Draven!"

Draven: "Do not waste the hit. Finish it."

Post-Mission Outcome
The Twinfang Chief falls. In the quiet after battle, the party uncovers sealed orders naming Aric's unit expendable.

Lyria: "Aric..."

Aric reads the signature and goes still.

Aric: "No. There is an explanation. There has to be."

Kain: "There usually is. It is just never a kind one."

Aric folds the document with deliberate care.

Aric: "We return to the capital. I will hear the truth from his own mouth."


FINALE CUTSCENE 001
Cutscene ID: c1_return_and_honor
Location: Capital court
Cast: Full party, The Lord Marshall, assembled court

Visual Direction
Mirror the opening ceremony, but with colder color grading beneath the gold. Splendor should feel suspect now.

Script
The Lord Marshall: "Behold the heroes of Cinder Keep. Behold the shield of the realm."

Citizens cheer. Flower petals fall.

The Lord Marshall embraces Aric.

The Lord Marshall, low: "I knew you would endure."

Aric does not return the embrace immediately.


FINALE CUTSCENE 002
Cutscene ID: c1_private_audience
Location: Descent beneath Cinder Keep
Cast: Full party, The Lord Marshall

The Lord Marshall: "A final cleansing remains. A greater evil sleeps beneath the keep. Only your company has the strength to end it."

Sera: "Then why send no priesthood, no wardens, no engineers?"

The Lord Marshall: "Because I require certainty, not committee."

The chamber doors open onto ancient runes pulsing like buried heartbeats.


FINALE CUTSCENE 003
Cutscene ID: c1_deception
Location: Hidden ritual chamber

Red rune-chains erupt from the floor and bind the party.

Aric: "This is no demon ward."

The Lord Marshall: "No. It is a threshold."

Aric: "You used us."

The Lord Marshall: "I used history. You were merely its finest instrument."

Lyria: "He loved you."

The Lord Marshall: "And because he did, he never wavered. Loyalty is the purest key."

Sera: "You dressed evil as duty. There is no grace left in you."

Kain: "I told you kings lie. I just hoped this one did not."


FINALE CUTSCENE 004
Cutscene ID: c1_escape_and_loss
Location: Collapsing ritual chamber

Vex steps from shadow and drives his cursed blade into the core sigil.

Vex: "You mistake chains for control."

The rune lock shatters. The chamber begins to collapse.

Aric: "Vex, with us!"

Vex: "Go."

Zephyr holds a falling arch with storm pressure.

Zephyr: "I would like it noted that this counts as heroic restraint."

Mirel: "Move first. Joke later."

Kain glances back through smoke but cannot see Vex.


FINALE CUTSCENE 005
Cutscene ID: c1_second_march
Location: Exterior of Cinder Keep

The sky tears open with a crimson fracture over the keep.

The Lord Marshall's Voice: "Let the second march begin."

Lyria, shaken: "What do we do now?"

Aric, looking up at the wound in the sky: "Now we tell the truth. Then we stop him."

Final Shot
Two distant silhouettes watch the fracture from a black ridge far beyond the ruin.

